1. Privacy Policy
Last Updated: March 19, 2026

1. Data Collection
The Wall Check Bot ("the Bot") collects limited data to provide leaderboard and logging functionality. This includes:

Discord User IDs and Usernames: Collected when a user interacts with a button (e.g., "Wall Checked") or executes a command.

Timestamped Activity: We log the time and date of your interactions to calculate leaderboard standings.

Message Content: The Bot only "reads" messages that start with its specific command prefix or are part of a button interaction.

2. Use of Data
Collected data is used exclusively for:

Generating the "Wall Check Leaderboard."

Providing faction administrators with activity logs for security purposes.

Sending automated reminders to designated channels.

3. Data Storage and Security
Data is stored in CSV and JSON formats on secured servers provided by PythonAnywhere. We do not sell, trade, or share this data with third parties.

4. Data Deletion
Users may request the removal of their data from the logs at any time. To request deletion, please contact [Your Contact Info/Discord Tag]. Faction administrators also have the ability to wipe server-wide logs using the /resetwallstats command.
